HEADWORD: Schnorrer
<hw>Schnor"rer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Yiddish, fr.
G. <ets>schnurrer</ets>, fr. <ets>schnurren</ets> to hum, whir, hence,
from the sound of the musical instrument used by strolling beggars, to
beg.]</ety> <def>Among the Jews, a beggar.</def>⟦br⟧
